# Identity Operating System

> An open framework for agentic AI collaboration built on identity as the foundational primitive.

---

## Vision

We are building an **Identity Operating System** — a product-strategy-platform designed to make identity the atomic unit of trust, context, and collaboration across human and AI agents.

In the same way a traditional operating system abstracts hardware and provides primitives (processes, memory, I/O) to applications, the Identity OS provides **identity primitives** that applications, AI agents, and people can build upon: verified identity, delegated authority, contextual presence, and collaborative intent.

---

## Core Principles

| Principle | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Identity-first** | Every action, every resource access, and every collaboration starts with a verified identity — human or AI. |
| **Agentic by design** | AI agents are first-class citizens. They carry identity, accumulate context, and can delegate authority within explicit bounds. |
| **Composable trust** | Trust is not binary. It is composable, contextual, and time-bounded. |
| **Open collaboration** | Humans and agents collaborate symmetrically, with transparent intent and auditable history. |
| **Mission-driven** | Every product decision maps back to the platform mission: *democratise trusted collaboration for humans and AI*. |

